WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.235 --> 00:00:02.837
[Franklin]
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:02.971 --> 00:00:04.639
Amanda meant something
to all of us. so get your head
out of your ass.

3
00:00:04.772 --> 00:00:06.306
You've been pregnant
for three years.

4
00:00:06.440 --> 00:00:08.041
I can't remember a time
when you weren't pregnant.

5
00:00:08.175 --> 00:00:10.678
I'm sorry. is my pregnancy hard
on you two?

6
00:00:10.812 --> 00:00:14.782
The other girls.
I'm trying to help them too.
Who was doing this?

7
00:00:14.916 --> 00:00:19.386
There were bad. bad men.
They gave me this.

8
00:00:20.220 --> 00:00:22.524
House is clear. The girls
have been moved again.

9
00:00:22.657 --> 00:00:25.560
All this work. and we're still
one step behind.

10
00:00:33.501 --> 00:00:34.769
[♪ upbeat music playing]

11
00:00:36.938 --> 00:00:38.238
Dude. hurry up.

12
00:00:39.908 --> 00:00:41.809
Take it easy. Lizzie.
I can't rush nature.

13
00:00:43.310 --> 00:00:45.713
She's right. man.
How much do you have in you?

14
00:00:46.213 --> 00:00:47.447
[siren blares]

15
00:00:48.148 --> 00:00:49.182
[siren blares]

16
00:00:52.386 --> 00:00:53.888
[♪ upbeat music ends]

17
00:00:54.022 --> 00:00:56.390
Okay. everyone. just stay calm.
We didn't do anything wrong.

18
00:00:56.524 --> 00:00:58.158
What Nick is doing is
against the law.

19
00:00:58.292 --> 00:01:00.360
I'm not getting a ticket
because your boyfriend has
a weak bladder.

20
00:01:00.494 --> 00:01:01.529
Nick is not my boyfriend.

21
00:01:04.398 --> 00:01:05.432
[thuds]

22
00:01:06.801 --> 00:01:09.202
All of you.
step out of the car.

23
00:01:09.336 --> 00:01:11.138
I'm sorry. Officer.
our friend couldn't wait.

24
00:01:11.271 --> 00:01:12.907
and the nearest restroom
is really far--

25
00:01:13.041 --> 00:01:14.141
Get out of the car!

26
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:22.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

27
00:01:28.022 --> 00:01:30.725
-Nick.
-It'll be okay. I promise.

28
00:01:31.526 --> 00:01:33.828
Look. you can't just detain us.
We know our rights.

29
00:01:36.396 --> 00:01:38.231
-[grunts]
-[♪ "Ain't That
Peculiar" playing]

30
00:01:38.365 --> 00:01:41.035
[crowd cheering]

31
00:01:42.302 --> 00:01:43.571
Go. go. go. go. go.

32
00:01:44.606 --> 00:01:46.139
All right!

33
00:01:46.273 --> 00:01:50.612
♪ <i>Honey. you do me wrong</i>
<i>But still I'm crazy about you</i> ♪

34
00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:56.017
[Angie] Yes!
Move. move. move. move.

35
00:01:56.584 --> 00:01:58.118
-[crowd clapping]
-Safe.

36
00:01:58.251 --> 00:01:59.554
♪ <i>Every chance you get</i> ♪

37
00:01:59.687 --> 00:02:01.789
♪ <i>You seem to hurt me</i>
<i>More and more</i> ♪

38
00:02:01.923 --> 00:02:04.759
One more run. we tie this up.
we taking the extra innings.

39
00:02:04.892 --> 00:02:06.293
Yeah. baby.

40
00:02:06.426 --> 00:02:07.829
[Heller] Who's up?

41
00:02:08.395 --> 00:02:09.429
Oh. no.

42
00:02:10.598 --> 00:02:12.667
Trent. you're up.

43
00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:14.869
[cheering]

44
00:02:15.003 --> 00:02:16.838
[Heller] Come on.
come on. come on. come on.

45
00:02:19.741 --> 00:02:21.509
[Seth] Bring it in. everybody.
bring it in.

46
00:02:22.844 --> 00:02:25.079
Okay. real nice.

47
00:02:25.212 --> 00:02:26.681
Just do your best.

48
00:02:26.814 --> 00:02:30.051
Hey. can we start now?
Hey. Pete. Can we get
a pinch hitter?

49
00:02:30.183 --> 00:02:31.451
No. he's got it this time.

50
00:02:31.586 --> 00:02:33.021
You got it this time.
Right. Will?

51
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.488
-Let's go!
-Come on. baby!

52
00:02:35.389 --> 00:02:38.126
-[Pete]
Keep this game alive. Trent.
-[Heller] Bring us home. Will!

53
00:02:38.258 --> 00:02:41.161
Knees bent. eye on the ball.
You're looking good. son.

54
00:02:41.294 --> 00:02:43.965
-[Michael] Go. Will.
-[crowd clapping]

55
00:02:45.066 --> 00:02:46.768
-[crowd sighs]
-[Pete] Strike one.

56
00:02:46.901 --> 00:02:47.869
All right. It's okay.

57
00:02:48.002 --> 00:02:49.037
Sorry. Will.

58
00:02:49.604 --> 00:02:50.638
It's okay. Pete.

59
00:02:51.105 --> 00:02:55.009
-It's not you. it's me.
-[crowd chattering]

60
00:02:56.811 --> 00:02:58.345
-[crowd gasps]
-Strike two.

61
00:02:58.478 --> 00:02:59.681
You suck. Trent!

62
00:02:59.814 --> 00:03:01.248
We're on the same team.

63
00:03:01.883 --> 00:03:05.119
Don't swing unless it's yours.
and don't chase the ball.

64
00:03:05.252 --> 00:03:07.088
Awful lot of "don'ts"
in this game.

65
00:03:07.220 --> 00:03:08.288
[♪ music resumes]

66
00:03:10.424 --> 00:03:11.358
[grunts]

67
00:03:11.491 --> 00:03:12.527
[crowd cheering]

68
00:03:15.228 --> 00:03:16.898
Will! Come on. Let's go!

69
00:03:17.031 --> 00:03:20.467
-Trent. Trent! Run. run!
-Oh. Okay.

70
00:03:20.601 --> 00:03:22.302
<i>♪ I know love can last</i>
<i>Through years</i> ♪

71
00:03:22.436 --> 00:03:25.472
♪ <i>But how can love last</i>
<i>Through tears</i> ♪

72
00:03:25.606 --> 00:03:27.909
♪ <i>Tears. tears. tears</i> ♪

73
00:03:28.042 --> 00:03:30.511
♪ <i>Now ain't that</i>
<i>Peculiar baby</i> ♪

74
00:03:31.979 --> 00:03:32.947
Nice catch. babe.

75
00:03:33.081 --> 00:03:34.916
-Thanks. hon.
-[Angie] Yep.

76
00:03:35.049 --> 00:03:36.718
Good job. guys.
Well done. everybody.

77
00:03:36.851 --> 00:03:39.921
My son's first game.
and he made contact!

78
00:03:41.488 --> 00:03:43.256
-You did great!
-Thanks.

79
00:03:45.358 --> 00:03:46.828
[sighs]

80
00:03:46.961 --> 00:03:48.896
No. but don't feel bad. Don't
beat yourself up about it.

81
00:03:49.030 --> 00:03:50.397
[Michael]
No. you should feel very bad.

82
00:03:50.531 --> 00:03:52.033
[Faith] Did you put money
on this game?

83
00:03:52.166 --> 00:03:54.869
You did. didn't you?
Lucky haircut my ass.

84
00:03:55.002 --> 00:03:59.040
Well. excuse me
for having faith in our team
to the tune of $300.

85
00:03:59.173 --> 00:04:01.341
300? That's a whole lot
of beef jerky.

86
00:04:01.475 --> 00:04:02.944
Whatever will you do?

87
00:04:03.077 --> 00:04:04.411
Haven't you ever seen
<i>Rudy.</i> Trent?

88
00:04:04.545 --> 00:04:06.379
The talentless nerd is supposed
to come through in the end.

89
00:04:06.514 --> 00:04:07.749
[Lizzie's friend] She didn't do
anything wrong.

90
00:04:07.882 --> 00:04:09.584
-This is ridiculous.
-We were there.

91
00:04:09.717 --> 00:04:11.284
Polaski. Heller's not back yet.

92
00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.286
-and they won't listen to me.
-Where is she?

93
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:15.089
-You're hiding something.
-Hey. hey. hey.

94
00:04:15.223 --> 00:04:18.226
Inside voices. One of you.
tell me what happened.

95
00:04:18.358 --> 00:04:20.393
Police misconduct. unlawful
arrest... Take your pick.

96
00:04:20.528 --> 00:04:22.130
[Lizzie's friend] Two cops took
our friend for no reason.

97
00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:24.431
They made us get out of my car.
called Lizzie by name.

98
00:04:24.565 --> 00:04:27.101
then they cuffed her.
shoved her in the back
of their car. and took off.

99
00:04:27.235 --> 00:04:28.435
And now this woman's lying
about it.

100
00:04:28.569 --> 00:04:30.470
There's no Lizzie Lassen
in our system.

101
00:04:30.605 --> 00:04:33.406
Maybe she hasn't been processed
yet. I'll check
with highway patrol.

102
00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:36.276
Hey.

103
00:04:37.145 --> 00:04:40.114
-Did the officer do that
to you?
-One of 'em. yeah.

104
00:04:40.748 --> 00:04:42.583
I tried to help--

105
00:04:42.717 --> 00:04:44.986
They hit him in the head
with their cop stick. then
kicked the crap out of him.

106
00:04:46.687 --> 00:04:48.856
Okay. Officer Amos.
can you get a medic. please?

107
00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:52.627
No. no. I don't need it.
N-Nothing's broken. I can tell.

108
00:04:53.261 --> 00:04:54.294
You mind if I take a look?

109
00:04:57.131 --> 00:04:58.166
Yeah. yeah.

110
00:05:01.002 --> 00:05:02.136
[♪ tense music plays]

111
00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:04.205
Oh. yeah. Can I see the shirt?

112
00:05:07.642 --> 00:05:09.010
Fabric ripped clean.

113
00:05:09.510 --> 00:05:12.113
No scuffs. no smears
you get from tactical boots.

114
00:05:12.246 --> 00:05:15.348
This was made
by hard sole and narrow toe.

115
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:18.753
Um. were they wearing shoes
like those?

116
00:05:21.189 --> 00:05:22.990
-I don't know.
-They were nothing like those.

117
00:05:23.124 --> 00:05:25.026
More of a patent
leather Oxford cap toe.

118
00:05:26.260 --> 00:05:27.628
I'm a fashion design major.

119
00:05:27.762 --> 00:05:29.664
Okay. well.
what about the uniform?

120
00:05:29.797 --> 00:05:32.399
Did they have a badge number?
Any physical details?

121
00:05:32.533 --> 00:05:34.302
No. they were
just regular cop uniforms.

122
00:05:34.434 --> 00:05:36.804
I asked for
their badge numbers.
and they told me to shut up.

123
00:05:36.938 --> 00:05:38.773
Okay. we're gonna take
your statements.

124
00:05:38.906 --> 00:05:39.974
Come on.

125
00:05:45.980 --> 00:05:47.148
Hey. wait.

126
00:05:49.617 --> 00:05:51.686
-Did they call it in?
-Call what in?

127
00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:53.087
The car stop.

128
00:05:53.221 --> 00:05:55.656
Did you hear them running
your plates over the car radio?

129
00:05:56.190 --> 00:05:59.093
Did they say anything
into their shoulder mics?

130
00:05:59.227 --> 00:06:01.461
No. they didn't use
their radios at all.

131
00:06:01.596 --> 00:06:03.363
They just took Lizzie and left.

132
00:06:03.496 --> 00:06:05.666
Those don't sound
like police officers.

133
00:06:06.968 --> 00:06:10.104
I'm sorry. but I believe your
friend Lizzie was kidnapped.

134
00:06:10.238 --> 00:06:11.606
[♪ tense music ends]

135
00:06:13.808 --> 00:06:16.077
The people who took
your daughter knew her name.

136
00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:18.579
They could be using her
as a bargaining chip.

137
00:06:18.713 --> 00:06:20.181
Why haven't they contacted us?

138
00:06:20.314 --> 00:06:23.851
I'm not sure. but we can have
GBI techs monitor your devices.

139
00:06:23.985 --> 00:06:26.687
so we'll be able to track them
when they do reach out.

140
00:06:28.789 --> 00:06:32.492
Mrs. Lassen. why don't you tell
me about Lizzie?
What's she like?

141
00:06:34.662 --> 00:06:37.064
She's kind. responsible.

142
00:06:38.266 --> 00:06:40.768
volunteers in a million groups
at college. Um...

143
00:06:41.235 --> 00:06:42.770
She doesn't have any enemies.

144
00:06:42.904 --> 00:06:46.908
Can you think of anyone
who might wanna target
either of you?

145
00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:49.777
Personal. business reasons.

146
00:06:49.911 --> 00:06:54.849
Dr. Lassen. it could be
a patient. maybe someone
with insurance issues.

147
00:06:54.982 --> 00:06:56.717
I shifted my practice
years ago.

148
00:06:56.851 --> 00:07:00.087
I'm a concierge doctor now.
highly-personalized care.

149
00:07:00.221 --> 00:07:03.758
My clients pay me a retainer
fee. zero complaints.

150
00:07:05.293 --> 00:07:06.594
What about that nurse?

151
00:07:07.695 --> 00:07:09.563
You know who I'm talking about?
At the hospital.

152
00:07:09.697 --> 00:07:11.198
Hon. that was years ago.

153
00:07:11.332 --> 00:07:14.434
Uh. was that when you worked
at Atlanta District Hospital?

154
00:07:15.002 --> 00:07:16.404
What happened?

155
00:07:16.537 --> 00:07:19.240
She was stealing pain meds.
and Eugene had to fire her.

156
00:07:19.373 --> 00:07:21.075
-[♪ tense music plays]
-She was really angry.

157
00:07:21.208 --> 00:07:24.111
She sent us all those emails.
remember? They were nasty.

158
00:07:24.645 --> 00:07:27.214
I seriously doubt
she's involved in this.

159
00:07:27.348 --> 00:07:30.251
It wouldn't make any sense
for her to show up out
of the blue and take Lizzie.

160
00:07:30.384 --> 00:07:32.286
So we just have no idea
who did this?

161
00:07:36.123 --> 00:07:38.559
-I think I need. like.
curry or something.
-Hey. guys.

162
00:07:38.693 --> 00:07:40.328
Guys. Priya said that a
motorcyclist with a helmet cam

163
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:41.896
slowed down to watch the stop.

164
00:07:42.029 --> 00:07:43.998
-Got the video.
-Good job.

165
00:07:44.765 --> 00:07:45.967
Hey. does that help?

166
00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:48.369
It's supposed to coax her down
into my pelvis.

167
00:07:48.502 --> 00:07:50.838
I'm so done being pregnant.
I'm trying to evict this child.

168
00:07:50.972 --> 00:07:52.606
Okay. Here we go.

169
00:07:55.843 --> 00:07:58.980
Dodge Charger. It looks close.
but that's about four
or five years too old.

170
00:07:59.113 --> 00:08:00.448
[Angie] Yeah. not ours.

171
00:08:00.581 --> 00:08:02.616
I can't make out
a license plate. Nothing.

172
00:08:03.517 --> 00:08:07.788
Wait. wait. Okay.
look at their uniforms.
They look right. but not right.

173
00:08:09.623 --> 00:08:11.158
It's the stripes. You see that?

174
00:08:11.292 --> 00:08:12.960
That gray stripe
going down the outer pant leg?

175
00:08:13.094 --> 00:08:15.863
-[Angie]
Yeah. definitely not APD.
-Hold on. why do I know this?

176
00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:20.001
Uh. I got it. It's Roy Gray.

177
00:08:20.801 --> 00:08:23.037
Roy Gray is the lead detective
of <i>Shades of Gray.</i>

178
00:08:23.170 --> 00:08:25.139
-Cop show. films in Atlanta.
-I don't know it.

179
00:08:25.272 --> 00:08:26.807
Oh. girl. it's so good.
You gotta watch it.

180
00:08:26.941 --> 00:08:28.676
-Is it accurate?
-Oh. God. no.

181
00:08:28.809 --> 00:08:30.478
[Angie chuckles]

182
00:08:30.611 --> 00:08:32.980
All right.
sounds like you guys need to
take a field trip over there.

183
00:08:33.114 --> 00:08:34.982
<i>Shades of Gray.</i>

184
00:08:35.116 --> 00:08:38.552
I've got the nurse who had beef
with Lassen coming in
for an interview. so bye.

185
00:08:38.686 --> 00:08:42.089
Okay. Bye. babe.
Work those hips. girl.

186
00:08:43.057 --> 00:08:45.159
Ms. McCaffrey. Hi.

187
00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:48.829
I'm Detective Polaski.
Thanks so much for coming in.

188
00:08:49.864 --> 00:08:52.199
Jeez. Good for you.

189
00:08:52.333 --> 00:08:54.668
-What. 39 weeks?
-Yeah.

190
00:08:55.369 --> 00:08:56.370
I was an OB nurse.

191
00:08:57.371 --> 00:08:58.372
Yeah.

192
00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:00.509
[clicks tongue] I know.

193
00:09:02.376 --> 00:09:05.312
You've gotta be kidding me.
Is that what this is about?

194
00:09:06.213 --> 00:09:07.782
I do need to ask you
some questions

195
00:09:07.915 --> 00:09:10.051
regarding the incident
which resulted in your firing.

196
00:09:10.184 --> 00:09:11.852
You mean that ruined my life?

197
00:09:11.986 --> 00:09:13.888
Sure. let's keep
rehashing that.

198
00:09:14.021 --> 00:09:18.192
Why not? For the millionth
time. I never stole drugs.

199
00:09:18.959 --> 00:09:20.761
But it was Lassen's word
over mine.

200
00:09:20.895 --> 00:09:23.431
Dr. Lassen was the one
who accused you of stealing?

201
00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:25.299
-[♪ dramatic music plays]
-Accused me?

202
00:09:25.433 --> 00:09:28.069
Honey. he set me up
because he was the one stealing
drugs from the hospital.

203
00:09:30.604 --> 00:09:32.907
Gwen McCaffrey is still pissed

204
00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:36.343
and swears it was Eugene
who stole the drugs.

205
00:09:36.477 --> 00:09:37.878
She says she knows
how much he was making.

206
00:09:38.012 --> 00:09:39.447
and he was living
way beyond his means.

207
00:09:39.580 --> 00:09:41.115
That tracks with
what Will found.

208
00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:44.852
Lassen paid cash.
literal cash. for a very
expensive luxury car.

209
00:09:44.985 --> 00:09:47.221
And two months ago.
he opened a new bank account.

210
00:09:47.354 --> 00:09:49.090
He did?
His wife's name's not on it?

211
00:09:49.223 --> 00:09:52.660
Just him. and the initial
deposit was almost double
his reported salary.

212
00:09:52.793 --> 00:09:54.128
He's into something.

213
00:09:55.396 --> 00:09:57.631
-Something that got
his daughter taken.
-[elevator bell dings]

214
00:10:00.401 --> 00:10:03.804
Here it is. Every costume
logged in. logged out.

215
00:10:03.938 --> 00:10:05.306
This is the log.

216
00:10:05.439 --> 00:10:07.241
How many full sets of police
uniforms do you have on hand?

217
00:10:07.374 --> 00:10:09.143
Eight. Are we done?

218
00:10:09.276 --> 00:10:10.579
[Franklin] Your log is amazing.

219
00:10:10.711 --> 00:10:13.647
I respect the hell out of that
log. and the woman who made it.

220
00:10:13.781 --> 00:10:17.284
But a young lady's
been kidnapped by people
wearing your uniforms.

221
00:10:18.085 --> 00:10:19.554
We need to do
a physical count. yes?

222
00:10:21.789 --> 00:10:23.691
-Over here.
-Thank you.

223
00:10:25.493 --> 00:10:30.231
One. two. three. four... six.

224
00:10:30.364 --> 00:10:31.465
[♪ tense music plays]

225
00:10:36.804 --> 00:10:38.072
I'll be back.

226
00:10:39.608 --> 00:10:41.342
Well...

227
00:10:41.475 --> 00:10:44.178
[shopkeeper] This was
on our security footage.
That man does not work for me.

228
00:10:44.311 --> 00:10:46.247
That's one of the kids
from the car.

229
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.048
Yeah. Lizzie's friend.

230
00:10:48.916 --> 00:10:50.117
That's Nick.

231
00:10:51.586 --> 00:10:52.753
[♪ tense music stops]

232
00:10:55.322 --> 00:10:56.457
[Faith] Hey.

233
00:10:57.124 --> 00:11:00.461
The other kids
from the car checked out.
They aren't a part of this.

234
00:11:01.162 --> 00:11:02.796
This stuff
from Nick's apartment?

235
00:11:03.464 --> 00:11:06.467
Yeah. unis said
it was barely furnished.

236
00:11:06.601 --> 00:11:08.802
-He'd. uh. been sleeping
on a yoga mat.
-[paper rustles]

237
00:11:12.541 --> 00:11:13.575
Tired?

238
00:11:16.578 --> 00:11:18.345
More like sleepwalking.

239
00:11:19.548 --> 00:11:20.681
I don't know.

240
00:11:21.482 --> 00:11:25.486
World feels kind of dull.
Like some lights went out.

241
00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:29.256
Yeah. it's the same feeling
I had when my dad died.

242
00:11:31.091 --> 00:11:33.060
When did that feeling go away?

243
00:11:33.794 --> 00:11:34.828
It doesn't.

244
00:11:36.030 --> 00:11:38.533
But then other things come
into your life.

245
00:11:38.667 --> 00:11:42.336
and one day you realize
that it doesn't hurt as bad.

246
00:11:43.638 --> 00:11:45.206
Multiple collection notices.

247
00:11:45.339 --> 00:11:47.808
Two maxed out credit cards. His
power was about to shut off.

248
00:11:47.942 --> 00:11:49.877
Well. maybe we don't need
to overthink motive.

249
00:11:50.010 --> 00:11:52.913
Exactly. Did the techs unlock
this yet?

250
00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:58.252
I've been. uh.
reading. or listening.
to Nick's juvie file.

251
00:11:58.385 --> 00:12:03.757
At 16. he beat a man
unconscious behind a strip mall
off Piedmont.

252
00:12:03.891 --> 00:12:07.027
Aggravated assault charges were
reduced because of his age.

253
00:12:07.161 --> 00:12:08.229
And what set him off?

254
00:12:08.796 --> 00:12:10.864
Well. the victim said they'd
never seen each other before.

255
00:12:14.235 --> 00:12:17.004
Nick was looking
at foreclosed properties.

256
00:12:17.137 --> 00:12:18.939
He bookmarked several of them.

257
00:12:21.375 --> 00:12:23.210
Maybe he's using one of 'em
to hold Lizzie.

258
00:12:23.344 --> 00:12:25.379
-Yeah.
-[♪ suspenseful music plays]

259
00:12:27.915 --> 00:12:28.949
Will.

260
00:12:30.251 --> 00:12:34.488
[sobs] <i>Whatever they asked you</i>
<i>for. please give it to them.</i>

261
00:12:35.222 --> 00:12:39.561
<i>I'm safe for now. but they say</i>
<i>our time is running out.</i>

262
00:12:40.361 --> 00:12:41.395
[Lizzie panting]

263
00:12:42.564 --> 00:12:45.032
I am so sorry. Mrs. Lassen.

264
00:12:45.799 --> 00:12:47.234
You haven't seen this before?

265
00:12:47.736 --> 00:12:48.769
No.

266
00:12:49.837 --> 00:12:51.205
She's so pale.

267
00:12:52.773 --> 00:12:55.009
What does that mean?
"Whatever they asked for"?

268
00:12:55.142 --> 00:12:57.811
You haven't heard of any ransom
demand or anything like that?

269
00:12:57.945 --> 00:12:59.648
-No.
-[♪ suspenseful music ends]

270
00:12:59.780 --> 00:13:01.315
Not unless Eugene received one.

271
00:13:02.316 --> 00:13:03.417
Where's your husband now?

272
00:13:05.052 --> 00:13:06.621
I don't know.

273
00:13:06.755 --> 00:13:08.989
I've been calling him all day.
He's not answering his phone.

274
00:13:11.925 --> 00:13:12.993
Mrs. Lassen.

275
00:13:13.728 --> 00:13:14.795
It's just...

276
00:13:15.730 --> 00:13:17.197
I checked the bedroom safe.

277
00:13:17.331 --> 00:13:18.465
[♪ eerie music plays]

278
00:13:19.233 --> 00:13:20.635
And I did notice...

279
00:13:22.537 --> 00:13:23.772
his gun is gone.

280
00:13:26.473 --> 00:13:30.144
A scared dad with a gun. Talk
about a recipe for disaster.

281
00:13:30.277 --> 00:13:32.479
Not unless he knows how to
shoot. Haven't you seen <i>Taken?</i>

282
00:13:33.013 --> 00:13:35.149
Everyone thinks they're
Liam Neeson. No one is.

283
00:13:36.250 --> 00:13:37.885
Hey. here's a weird one.

284
00:13:38.018 --> 00:13:40.454
This is a list of the meds
stolen from the hospital
where Eugene worked.

285
00:13:40.588 --> 00:13:43.792
It's oxy. hydrocodone.
the usual suspects.

286
00:13:43.924 --> 00:13:47.861
and then a large quantity
of morning-after pills
and antiviral meds.

287
00:13:48.697 --> 00:13:49.997
Like. for STDs?

288
00:13:50.130 --> 00:13:53.033
Yeah. but they have zero street
value. so why steal them?

289
00:13:53.167 --> 00:13:55.235
We pulled something
from the ransom video.

290
00:13:56.771 --> 00:13:58.172
What am I looking at here?

291
00:13:58.305 --> 00:14:00.274
The stub coming from the wall.
That's a capped gas line.

292
00:14:00.407 --> 00:14:02.176
They were used
to feed wall-mounted sconces

293
00:14:02.309 --> 00:14:04.679
before buildings
were wired for electricity.

294
00:14:05.446 --> 00:14:06.447
[Angie] So the building's old?

295
00:14:06.581 --> 00:14:08.982
Pre-1890s.
Not many left in Atlanta.

296
00:14:09.718 --> 00:14:12.052
Uh. here's one
in his bookmarks.

297
00:14:12.620 --> 00:14:15.989
Built 1870. West End.

298
00:14:16.123 --> 00:14:17.525
[♪ adventurous music plays]

299
00:14:32.973 --> 00:14:33.907
[screeches]

300
00:14:34.041 --> 00:14:35.175
[speaking indistinctly]

301
00:14:40.481 --> 00:14:42.851
GBI. don't move.
Hands where I can see 'em.

302
00:14:44.885 --> 00:14:48.455
Lizzie. Faith Mitchell
with the GBI. You're safe now.
Come with me.

303
00:14:53.561 --> 00:14:54.729
[Nick] Let's go!

304
00:14:57.931 --> 00:14:59.166
Faith.

305
00:14:59.768 --> 00:15:00.735
Hey. you all right?

306
00:15:00.869 --> 00:15:02.202
I'm okay. Get him.

307
00:15:11.345 --> 00:15:14.281
-[grunting. panting]
-Stay down!

308
00:15:22.022 --> 00:15:23.725
[♪ adventurous music ends]

309
00:15:25.894 --> 00:15:27.428
We checked your laptop.

310
00:15:28.429 --> 00:15:31.398
You were searching for
information on Eugene Lassen

311
00:15:31.533 --> 00:15:33.300
weeks before you even
met Lizzie.

312
00:15:33.434 --> 00:15:34.769
[Faith] Care to explain that?

313
00:15:35.436 --> 00:15:36.771
Not really.

314
00:15:36.905 --> 00:15:38.773
Well. here's your theory.
Tell me if I'm close.

315
00:15:39.908 --> 00:15:41.810
You knew
Lizzie's dad had money.

316
00:15:41.942 --> 00:15:43.912
so you targeted her.
seduced her.

317
00:15:44.044 --> 00:15:45.847
Seduced her? [scoffs]

318
00:15:45.979 --> 00:15:50.217
And convinced her to help you
stage her kidnapping
so you could rob her dad.

319
00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:54.556
I knew you cops were useless.

320
00:15:54.689 --> 00:15:57.257
but it's really something
to see it live.

321
00:15:57.391 --> 00:15:59.193
Who was the woman
she ran out with?

322
00:16:02.162 --> 00:16:03.964
You know. with your record.

323
00:16:04.097 --> 00:16:05.733
judge ain't gonna be easy
on you.

324
00:16:05.867 --> 00:16:07.669
No. they're gonna see
a pattern.

325
00:16:08.268 --> 00:16:13.407
A kid who seeks out volatile
situations and escalates them.

326
00:16:14.576 --> 00:16:17.779
Someone who targeted
a vulnerable young woman.

327
00:16:17.912 --> 00:16:20.648
Shut up. man!
Shut the hell up. all right?

328
00:16:20.782 --> 00:16:23.718
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

329
00:16:24.418 --> 00:16:26.186
Will. outside.

330
00:16:30.023 --> 00:16:32.326
The tattoo on his neck.
The V. Grace Elverton.

331
00:16:32.961 --> 00:16:34.629
Your sex trafficking case.

332
00:16:34.762 --> 00:16:37.197
She had the exact same one.
She said that her handler gave
it to her.

333
00:16:37.331 --> 00:16:40.367
The medication
that Eugene stole.
birth control. abortion drugs.

334
00:16:40.502 --> 00:16:43.838
He was treating girls.
keeping them healthy enough
to keep working.

335
00:16:43.972 --> 00:16:45.640
I think
that Nick was trafficked.

336
00:16:45.773 --> 00:16:48.977
It would explain his juvie
record. the fights. volatility.

337
00:16:49.109 --> 00:16:51.311
What we've been reading
as a pattern of aggression

338
00:16:51.445 --> 00:16:53.748
was actually
self-defense against--

339
00:16:53.882 --> 00:16:55.082
A rapist.

340
00:16:56.450 --> 00:16:57.819
Lizzie knew
what her dad was up to.

341
00:16:57.952 --> 00:17:00.220
She teamed up with Nick
to put a stop to it.

342
00:17:01.990 --> 00:17:03.223
I'm going back in there.

343
00:17:05.025 --> 00:17:06.059
[door opens]

344
00:17:06.861 --> 00:17:07.896
[door closes]

345
00:17:08.863 --> 00:17:10.097
I wanna help you.

346
00:17:10.698 --> 00:17:12.600
Whatever.

347
00:17:12.734 --> 00:17:14.602
Look. I know you think
you're doing the right thing.
but there's a better way.

348
00:17:14.736 --> 00:17:17.070
Oh. yeah?
Yeah. and what's that. huh?

349
00:17:17.204 --> 00:17:19.373
With you guys? Please. [scoffs]

350
00:17:26.748 --> 00:17:27.782
I know.

351
00:17:30.217 --> 00:17:32.185
Fulton Industrial Boulevard.

352
00:17:33.220 --> 00:17:35.188
On any night of the week.
you drive down that road.

353
00:17:35.322 --> 00:17:37.926
and you're gonna
to see kids lined up.

354
00:17:38.492 --> 00:17:42.062
Twelve. thirteen-year-old kids.
kids with baby teeth.

355
00:17:42.195 --> 00:17:44.032
girls with teddy bears.

356
00:17:44.866 --> 00:17:47.067
And guys just pull up
like it's a drive-through.

357
00:17:47.835 --> 00:17:50.203
Pimps watching.
drivers watching.

358
00:17:50.337 --> 00:17:52.172
motel clerks. landlords.

359
00:17:52.306 --> 00:17:54.509
But it's not their kid. right?

360
00:17:56.443 --> 00:17:58.880
-So who cares?
-I care.

361
00:18:02.717 --> 00:18:04.586
They're not even the worst
of it. you know?

362
00:18:06.020 --> 00:18:09.222
You've seen the files.
Everyone's seen the files.

363
00:18:09.356 --> 00:18:12.225
The billionaires.
the politicians.

364
00:18:12.359 --> 00:18:13.695
they're all. what? Just...

365
00:18:14.194 --> 00:18:16.731
fighting on television
for entertainment.

366
00:18:16.864 --> 00:18:21.703
but behind closed doors. it's
all "you help me. I help you."

367
00:18:23.236 --> 00:18:26.473
The man who writes the law
and the guy who breaks it
sitting at the same table.

368
00:18:27.809 --> 00:18:31.345
And the girl who nobody is
looking for is serving drinks.

369
00:18:34.348 --> 00:18:37.051
What were you trying to get
from Eugene Lassen?

370
00:18:40.588 --> 00:18:42.023
<i>Nick and Lizzie</i>
<i>aren't working alone.</i>

371
00:18:42.155 --> 00:18:44.025
There's a whole group of them.

372
00:18:44.157 --> 00:18:47.494
Most are survivors
of trafficking.
or they've lost someone to it.

373
00:18:47.629 --> 00:18:49.731
They feel like law enforcement
has failed them.

374
00:18:49.864 --> 00:18:51.733
so they decided to take matters
into their own hands.

375
00:18:51.866 --> 00:18:53.500
What are they after?

376
00:18:53.635 --> 00:18:55.637
Eugene's medical notes.
the ones that he kept
on the girls he treated.

377
00:18:55.770 --> 00:18:58.205
They're hoping
that it helps them ID the girls

378
00:18:58.338 --> 00:19:00.140
and track down the pedophiles.

379
00:19:00.273 --> 00:19:02.810
Nick was trafficked by the
same people who were holding
our alien girl. Grace?

380
00:19:02.944 --> 00:19:05.178
It's the same network.
but there are different tiers.

381
00:19:05.312 --> 00:19:06.848
They have
the street-level victims

382
00:19:06.981 --> 00:19:09.182
who work the motels
and truck stops.

383
00:19:09.316 --> 00:19:10.918
and then there are
the high-level girls.

384
00:19:11.052 --> 00:19:13.253
Those are the ones
that Eugene treats secretly.

385
00:19:13.387 --> 00:19:16.024
-Scumbag.
-The handoff is going down
this afternoon.

386
00:19:16.156 --> 00:19:19.661
The old metal yard
on Hollowell. Lizzie
in exchange for the notes.

387
00:19:19.794 --> 00:19:23.196
We will be there. let it
play out. intercept the notes.

388
00:19:23.330 --> 00:19:24.632
and then arrest Eugene.

389
00:19:25.566 --> 00:19:26.701
[hiccups]

390
00:19:26.834 --> 00:19:28.870
-Sorry. [chuckles]
-How spicy is that curry?

391
00:19:29.003 --> 00:19:30.805
My tongue burned completely off
ten minutes ago.

392
00:19:30.938 --> 00:19:33.041
but if it helps this baby come.
I don't need my taste buds.

393
00:19:33.608 --> 00:19:35.977
Wait. what about Lizzie?
She cracked your head open
with a lamp.

394
00:19:36.110 --> 00:19:39.346
My head is fine.
We will take her into
protective custody. No cuffs.

395
00:19:40.148 --> 00:19:41.849
[hiccups] Oh.

396
00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:44.852
-Girl. do you need me
to scare you?
-No. that...

397
00:19:44.986 --> 00:19:46.587
This is... This one was...

398
00:19:46.721 --> 00:19:48.756
That's not a hiccup.
This is happening. I think.

399
00:19:48.890 --> 00:19:50.892
[♪ upbeat music plays]

400
00:19:51.025 --> 00:19:53.127
-Well. it's about time.
-I will drive you myself.

401
00:19:53.260 --> 00:19:55.897
No. I will call my husband.
and he will drive me.

402
00:19:56.030 --> 00:19:58.166
and-and you will go get
the bad doctor.

403
00:19:58.298 --> 00:19:59.667
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

404
00:19:59.801 --> 00:20:01.636
-[Franklin] Are you good?
-You have a go bag?

405
00:20:01.769 --> 00:20:03.838
Yeah. it's at home.
but he's gonna get it.
It's gonna be great.

406
00:20:04.304 --> 00:20:05.940
-[all cheering]
-Yes.

407
00:20:06.074 --> 00:20:07.207
Oh.

408
00:20:07.340 --> 00:20:10.178
[sirens wailing]

409
00:20:11.478 --> 00:20:14.182
You and Faith are seriously
gonna cut this kid loose
after all this?

410
00:20:14.314 --> 00:20:15.717
Well. the group he's in.

411
00:20:15.850 --> 00:20:18.553
they have access we can't get
with badges and warrants.

412
00:20:18.686 --> 00:20:20.955
A bunch of untrained civilians
running their own ops.

413
00:20:21.089 --> 00:20:22.757
That's how people end up dead.

414
00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:24.659
It's Faith's case.
and she trusts the guy.

415
00:20:24.792 --> 00:20:26.060
I'm backing her play.

416
00:20:27.161 --> 00:20:28.763
It's what Amanda
would have done.

417
00:20:30.631 --> 00:20:33.101
[♪ tense music plays]

418
00:20:54.856 --> 00:20:56.456
Give me the notes!
Come on! Quick!

419
00:20:56.591 --> 00:20:58.226
[Faith] Those are the notes.

420
00:21:01.729 --> 00:21:02.764
[Franklin] Shooter.

421
00:21:02.897 --> 00:21:03.998
[Faith] He's taking them out.

422
00:21:04.132 --> 00:21:05.833
Down. down. down. down!

423
00:21:05.967 --> 00:21:07.400
I'll flank. Cover my back.

424
00:21:09.402 --> 00:21:11.271
APD! Put the weapon down now!

425
00:21:22.449 --> 00:21:25.452
We need an ambulance
at this location. Suspect shot.
currently unresponsive.

426
00:21:26.120 --> 00:21:27.255
It's clear!

427
00:21:28.689 --> 00:21:32.093
-Lizzie. Hey. are you okay?
-[panting] I'm fine.

428
00:21:32.226 --> 00:21:34.195
[♪ dramatic music plays]

429
00:21:35.062 --> 00:21:36.363
Lizzie. baby. thank God--

430
00:21:36.496 --> 00:21:38.666
I know what you and your
friends do. You make me sick.

431
00:21:39.267 --> 00:21:40.635
Wait. no. wait.

432
00:21:40.768 --> 00:21:42.737
This was you? I was terrified.
I thought you might be dead.

433
00:21:42.870 --> 00:21:45.338
What about all the
other parents who don't know
where their daughters are?

434
00:21:45.472 --> 00:21:46.541
You don't think they're scared?

435
00:21:46.674 --> 00:21:48.176
-Come on. Let's go.
-I didn't...

436
00:21:50.144 --> 00:21:52.180
You have no idea
the people you're dealing with.

437
00:21:57.552 --> 00:21:58.853
-[knocks on door]
-[Faith] <i>Come in.</i>

438
00:21:59.954 --> 00:22:00.855
-Hey.
-[Faith] Hey.

439
00:22:00.988 --> 00:22:02.489
How'd it go with Eugene?

440
00:22:02.623 --> 00:22:05.226
He lawyered up.
He's not giving us anything.

441
00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:08.162
He's more afraid of the people
he works for than he is of us.

442
00:22:08.296 --> 00:22:09.797
Oh. he should be.

443
00:22:09.931 --> 00:22:12.200
The shooter had
enough ammunition
to take out everyone there.

444
00:22:12.332 --> 00:22:15.002
I will bet you anything
he was sent by the traffickers

445
00:22:15.136 --> 00:22:17.772
to clean up Eugene and Nick.
Lizzie too.

446
00:22:17.905 --> 00:22:19.941
-You get anything
from the records?
-Oh. yeah.

447
00:22:20.074 --> 00:22:22.043
We pulled two addresses.
Sent teams.

448
00:22:22.176 --> 00:22:24.312
Found five girls at one.
four at the other.

449
00:22:24.444 --> 00:22:26.379
Arrested the homeowners.

450
00:22:26.514 --> 00:22:29.717
One was a private equity
manager. and the other was
a Georgia State Senator

451
00:22:29.851 --> 00:22:33.020
who shook my hand at a GBI
dedication ceremony last year.

452
00:22:34.454 --> 00:22:37.357
So a network full of powerful
men. He'll take it apart.

453
00:22:37.490 --> 00:22:38.526
[Michael scoffs]

454
00:22:40.027 --> 00:22:41.896
The GBI is
too politically connected

455
00:22:42.029 --> 00:22:44.031
for an investigation
to be successful.

456
00:22:46.634 --> 00:22:47.735
So find another way.

457
00:22:47.869 --> 00:22:50.304
[♪ upbeat music plays]

458
00:23:04.852 --> 00:23:08.055
Mitchell. what brings you down
to the APD?

459
00:23:08.522 --> 00:23:10.524
I've been at the GBI
for four years now.

460
00:23:10.658 --> 00:23:13.060
and I just wondered
if you guys miss me down here.

461
00:23:14.328 --> 00:23:15.763
What do you need?

462
00:23:17.865 --> 00:23:19.399
[♪ upbeat music ends]

463
00:23:20.801 --> 00:23:22.003
[Seth] Breathe through it.
You'll be fine.

464
00:23:22.136 --> 00:23:23.537
-[Angie] Okay.
-[Seth] Phone charger?

465
00:23:23.671 --> 00:23:26.741
-Check.
-Okay.
Little silver nipple hats?

466
00:23:27.275 --> 00:23:29.110
-Check.
-All right. Portable speaker?

467
00:23:29.243 --> 00:23:30.945
-[♪ "Blue" playing]
-[sighs]

468
00:23:31.078 --> 00:23:32.113
-Check.
-Great.

469
00:23:32.246 --> 00:23:33.614
Oh. I forgot to make
a birth playlist.

470
00:23:33.748 --> 00:23:35.549
-That's okay. I made three.
-You did?

471
00:23:35.683 --> 00:23:37.852
Uh. one for if you have
an epidural. It's mostly Enya.

472
00:23:38.352 --> 00:23:42.422
One for if you're just
raw-dogging it. and that's.
like. all riot grrrl.

473
00:23:42.556 --> 00:23:44.992
-[chuckles] Stop.
-[chuckles]
Then one for after the birth

474
00:23:45.126 --> 00:23:47.561
because it's never too early
to learn about Stevie Wonder.

